    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      UnloadAllChunksForced
      Unload ALL chunks in a world with force, keeping only ones loaded by players.
      UnloadAllChunksUnforced
      Unload all the chunks in a world that are not kept loaded by players or worldanchors.
      UnloadExtremeAlways
      Always: always unloads chunks; unloads as many as possible
      Extreme: unloads all chunks, does no checks.
      UnloadExtremeWhenForced
      Deprecated. 
      No one should use this, it makes no sense.
      UnloadExtremeWhenForced_Plus
      Deprecated. 
      No one should use this, it makes no sense.
      UnloadHighAlways
      Always: always unloads chunks; unloads as many as possible
      High: only chunks not kept loaded by players.
      UnloadHighWhenForced
      Forced: only unloads when forced; goes to limit, not below it
      High: only chunks not kept loaded by players.
      UnloadHighWhenForced_Plus
      Forced_Plus: only unloads when forced; goes to limit and x % below it
      High: only chunks not kept loaded by players.
      UnloadLowAlways
      Always: always unloads chunks; unloads as many as possible
      Low: only chunks not kept loaded by chunkloaders, players (radius x2), spawn
      UnloadLowWhenForced
      Forced: only unloads when forced; goes to limit, not below it
      Low: only chunks not kept loaded by chunkloaders, players (radius x2), spawn
      UnloadLowWhenForced_Plus
      Forced_Plus: only unloads when forced; goes to limit and x % below it
      Low: only chunks not kept loaded by chunkloaders, players (radius x2), spawn
      UnloadNormalAlways
      Always: always unloads chunks; unloads as many as possible
      Normal: only chunks not kept loaded by chunkloaders, players, spawn
      UnloadNormalWhenForced
      Forced: only unloads when forced; goes to limit, not below it
      Normal: only chunks not kept loaded by chunkloaders, players, spawn
      UnloadNormalWhenForced_Plus
      Forced_Plus: only unloads when forced; goes to limit and x % below it
      Normal: only chunks not kept loaded by chunkloaders, players, spawn
      UnloadUnforced
      Unload chunks until the total chunk amount is good again.
      Equal to unloading unforced first, and then AllChunkUnforced if it cannot lower enough.
      If this can still not get by the limit, it will also unload worldanchor chunks.
      UnloadWorldForced
      Unload ALL CHUNKS IN A WORLD no matter what.
